caption.text:
No gatekeeping here ⬇️

You know I don’t hold back, in the last 7 months, to grow 278,000 followers on Instagram I’ve made a point of doing the following:

I focus useful, relatable, saveable and sharable content, sales were not my primary focus.

I took the time to really get to know what’s working in my niche, instead of guessing.

I regularly Look at posts I’ve made that have done well and figured out ways to recreate them! (All my caption and hook writing content does well)

If you haven’t watched my 75 minute video lesson, this is going to really help get clear on finding out what’s working on Instagram, and take away all that uncertainty!

Most of all I show up, every day, even when I don’t feel like it, even when it’s hard and even when my kid spends 24 hours throwing up 🤣

#iggrowth #instagramgrowth #contentstrategy

Easy Trick to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new audiences, but stories are the best way to connect current followers….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- Tap and begin a new story, tap the camera button and slide through the filters along the bottom of the screen until you find the magnifying glass.

- Type in here background tablet, and use this filter. Press the shutter button to take a photograph and close the screen.

- Go to the reel, you would like to share, tap the aeroplane and share to story.

- Resize the reel in the left of the screen of the screen, now go to your stickers, tab, photo album, and add the tablet image you just created. Now the reel appears in front, and the photo behind.

- go to your text tab, choose your favourite phone and add some text to give the reel context. Explain to your followers what the reel is about.

- Go to your stickers tab, type “new reel black” and choose the sticker to place on top of the reel

- Now go to your stickers, tab, type click, choose your favourite, click, and place it over the top of the reel.

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

caption.text:
Instagram finally told us!

Instagram have spilled the tea….one of the main things they take into consideration when ranking and deciding what content to push to the algorithm is “sends per reach” aka Shares!

If you don’t know what that might look like for your account, really stop and think about your target audience….what’s going to relate to them.

Relatable content can take many shapes:

- Something that makes you feel seen that you’ll share “this is us”

- Content that makes you want to experience the same thing, a bed, a room or a destination and feels like “I want to do that too”

- Emotional content that you can relate to? An experience you’ve been through or cause that resonates with you strongly.

- Tutorial content, we all enjoy watching a process, and if it’s useful this content often gets shared. “I want to try this”

- Funny Content- audiences have short attention spans and if you can grab their attention with humour to reach out to them, they’ll often share with other similar audiences.

There are lots of other examples, but this is a great place to start brainstorming! I hope this is helpful and if you want help for your captions too, comment HOOKS below and I’ll share 100 free caption ideas for you to try and incorporate too!

caption.text:
Build audience curiosity ⬇️

Meta has confirmed “watch time” is a metric they measure within the Instagram algorithm,  when deciding what content to push out. This reel idea is a great way to increase watch time, and make an announcement or share a sneak peek.

Don’t forget to save this post as you won’t want to forget these steps! 

- tap and begin a new reel, choose any video you’d like to share, and go to your sparkles tab.

- Go to the magnifying glass, type in blue grid, and use the filter that I have used. 

- Go into your stickers tab, type loading, and choose your favourite loading status sticker. I used the white one and resized in the centre of the screen.

- Now you can add any text, go into your text tab, choose your favourite font, and ensure the background colour is switched on. Add any text to suit the theme of your video and resize to place right on top of that status bar sticker.

I’ve helped hundreds of you here with my Instagram resources, comment FREE for 5 free reels to try this week!

caption.text:
Trick 1,2 or3?!? 

We all get so focused on instagram growth, new followers and Reels it’s easy to forget your CURRENT followers and Instagram stories is the best place to do just that! 

Instagram Stories are the no1 way to build deeper connections with your current audience and getting them to like, know and trust you!

Here are my top 3 tricks to make Instagram stories feel easier! 

- don’t let filming location stop you, film in a stationary car!
- don’t let fear of what you look like stop you! Utilise daylight
- don’t let a lack of equipment stop you! Only a hairband needed

People buy from people they know like and trust and Stories is hands down the best place to start doing that!

Let me know if this was helpful! And maybe share with a fellow creator.

If you’re looking for a clearer idea of what stories are all about, comment CLASS and I’ll send you my 75 minute lesson that walks you through them in detail!!

caption.text:
Viral Instagram Filter 

This effect would work to liven up ANY image in your stories or Reels!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post, as you don’t want to forget the steps!

- tap and begin a new story, click camera layout, choose the four grid option and add any images of your choice. You could use product photos of the service you offer or even birthday images.

- Now slide through your filters, until you find the filter .Kodak film, if you can’t find it, I’ve saved it to this reel.

- Simply go into your text tab, choose the last font, and do a full stop with 15 spaces. Make sure your background colour is switched on, choose the colour picker and select a complementary within theimage

- Go to your stickers tab, type in black Polaroid, choose your favourite frame and place it righton the screen.

- Go to your stickers tab, select photo and add one of the original images, place on screen, tap to make it a square, and put it inside the frame.

- Go to your stickers tab, type link, add any WebLink you’d like and customise the text to suit. Now just hold down until you see the colour picker and colour the link sticker to compliment your design.

- Now anyone that taps, gets taken through to your site! This is such a simple hack, you’ll wonder how you’ve not used it before!

If you enjoyed this tip, I share new ideas like this every day to help you on your instagram growth journey! 

Share with someone else who loves to create new designs on Instagram!

caption.text:
Easy Hack to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new followers , but stories are the best way to connect to audiences….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- Tap and beginner new reel, add any photo you’d like to share, and press next. Go into your sparkles tab, and look for the filter “fashion shoot”, choose this filter, but zoom out slightly to move the effect down the screen and take a screenshot.

- Trim up the screenshot to turn your reel into an image.

- Go to the reel, you would like to share, tap the aeroplane and share to story.

- Resize the reel in the left of the screen of the screen, now go to your stickers, tab, photo album, and add the image you just created. Now the reel appears in front, and the photo behind.

- Go to your stickers tab, type “white reel” and choose the sticker to place on top of the reel

- Now go to your stickers, tab, type white click, choose your favourite, click, and place it over the top of the reel.

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

caption.text:
This is the truth…

I hear this complaint daily, you’re posting regularly because you know you have to, you heard somewhere that consistency is how you grow on instagram…you’re doing that, but still- nothing 

But it’s WHAT you post that matters! 

🚀Growth content- to spread awareness of you
🫶🏻Nurture content - getting followers like & trust you 
💰Conversion content - gets people buying or investing in you 

If you do not understand the different types of content

If you do not know why you should be using them

Then you will hugely benefit from my 75 minute class! Breaking everything down step by step, including the different content types and why you would use them, just comment CLASS and I’ll whiz over a link! 

Share with someone who needs to grow! 

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth
